  <subsection>
    <title>Exploring Other Coordinates</title>

    <p>
      In 3 dimensions, the most common coordinate systems are cylindrical and spherical. The equations for these coordinate systems are in the table below.
    </p>
    <table>
      <caption>Conversion between coordinate systems</caption>

      <tabular>
        <row>
          <cell>Cylindrical Coordinates</cell>
          <cell>Spherical Coordinates</cell>
        </row>
        <row bottom="minor">
          <cell></cell>
          <cell></cell>
        </row>
        <row>
          <cell><m>\begin{array}{l}
          x=r\cos\theta\\
          y=r\sin\theta\\
          z=z
          \end{array}</m></cell>
          <cell><m>\begin{array}{l}
          x=\rho\sin\phi\cos\theta\\
          y=\rho\sin\phi\sin\theta\\
          z=\rho\cos\phi
          \end{array}</m></cell>
        </row>
      </tabular>
    </table>

    <table>
      <caption></caption>
      <tabular>
        <row>
          <cell>Cylindrical Coordinates</cell>
          <cell>Spherical Coordinates(Math)</cell>
          <cell>Spherical (Physics/Engineering)</cell>
        </row>
        <row bottom="minor">
          <cell></cell>
          <cell></cell>
          <cell></cell>
        </row>
        <row>
          <cell><m>\begin{array}{l}
          x=r\cos\theta\\
          y=r\sin\theta\\
          z=z
          \end{array}</m></cell>
          <cell><m>\begin{array}{l}
          x=\rho\sin\theta\cos\phi\\
          y=\rho\sin\theta\sin\phi\\
          z=\rho\cos\theta
          \end{array}</m></cell>
          <cell><m>\begin{array}{l}
          x=r\sin\phi\cos\theta\\
          y=r\sin\phi\sin\theta\\
          z=r\cos\phi
          \end{array}</m></cell>
        </row>
      </tabular>
    </table>

